Raipur is a city in the Raipur district of the Indian state of Chhattisgarh. It is the capital city of the state of Chhattisgarh and is the administrative headquarters of Raipur district. It is also the largest city in Chhattisgarh. It was formerly a part of Madhya Pradesh before the state of Chhattisgarh was formed on 1 November 2000.Kawardha is a city and a municipality in Kabirdham district in the Indian state of Chhattisgarh. Kawardha is also known for the Temple of Bhoramdeo.